<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Shelton State Community College will award college credit for scores of 3 or higher on Advanced Placement examinations sponsored by the College Board. Students wishing to receive advanced placement credit should have the examination scores sent to the Admissions Office on the Martin Campus and then schedule a conference with a college counselor to determine the specific amount of credit to be awarded.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.sheltonstate.edu/admissions/general_information/ap_clep_ib_information.aspx" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

